WEBVTT

00:00:00.105 --> 00:00:03.665
(My dreams would be far too mysterious beyond anticipation.)

00:00:04.005 --> 00:00:06.993
(Because I lost my memories 10 years ago.)

00:00:07.185 --> 00:00:08.801
(You are back now, Botpleng?)

00:00:09.605 --> 00:00:10.881
(Can we meet?)

00:00:11.355 --> 00:00:14.073
I’m Tankhun, your lover.

00:00:14.113 --> 00:00:15.113
Are you the murderer?

00:00:15.515 --> 00:00:16.515
What do you think?

00:00:16.885 --> 00:00:19.297
The deceased just sent you a parcel.

00:00:19.785 --> 00:00:21.057
Then a week later,

00:00:21.405 --> 00:00:23.513
you became the one who found his body.

00:00:23.875 --> 00:00:25.251
Isn’t that too much of a coincidence?

00:00:25.275 --> 00:00:26.921
Are you suspecting me, Officer?

00:00:26.945 --> 00:00:28.585
Are you sure he’s not lying?

00:00:29.135 --> 00:00:30.135
For sure?

00:00:30.225 --> 00:00:31.225
Sure.

00:00:31.565 --> 00:00:33.871
Coming from the only body language decipherer of the department.

00:00:33.895 --> 00:00:36.353
Maybe you want to protect him

00:00:36.393 --> 00:00:37.561
due to personal reasons.

00:00:38.145 --> 00:00:39.681
You can’t remember me,

00:00:40.605 --> 00:00:41.737
but I can.

00:00:42.085 --> 00:00:44.849
I can remember who Botpleng’s first love is.

00:00:59.561 --> 00:01:00.561
Oh.

00:01:04.015 --> 00:01:05.609
I’ve got your clothes prepared.

00:01:07.605 --> 00:01:08.977
Wash up and get some rest.

00:01:13.305 --> 00:01:14.793
You’re right.

00:01:15.465 --> 00:01:17.049
When you said I’m not ready yet.

00:01:20.725 --> 00:01:21.793
I’m sorry.

00:01:28.845 --> 00:01:30.009
You don’t have to apologize.

00:01:30.555 --> 00:01:31.715
You didn’t do anything wrong.

00:01:32.245 --> 00:01:34.849
Also, I’ve waited for 10 years.

00:01:35.485 --> 00:01:36.753
Just waiting a little longer

00:01:36.777 --> 00:01:37.845
can’t hurt, right?

00:01:45.845 --> 00:01:46.845
Then…

00:01:49.005 --> 00:01:51.233
Can I hold your hand and sleep tonight?

00:01:52.375 --> 00:01:53.375
I think

00:01:53.625 --> 00:01:55.281
being close to you

00:01:56.153 --> 00:01:58.155
might make me remember you faster.

00:02:02.605 --> 00:02:04.401
I don’t want you to wait too long either.

00:04:27.005 --> 00:04:28.081
(He kissed me.)

00:04:28.825 --> 00:04:30.089
(We kissed.)

00:04:31.635 --> 00:04:33.897
(We couldn’t get enough.)

00:04:36.721 --> 00:04:38.881
(We learned about each other’s bodies.)

00:04:40.435 --> 00:04:43.041
(The feeling of touching his skin)

00:04:43.325 --> 00:04:45.129
(felt entirely different from my own.)

00:04:47.125 --> 00:04:49.705
(So does when he touched me.)

00:04:53.645 --> 00:04:57.217
(Tankhun has a long scar on his left wrist.)

00:04:58.735 --> 00:05:00.913
(I softly stroked that scar.)

00:05:03.045 --> 00:05:06.713
(Hoping that the pain in his heart
would subside.)

00:05:19.265 --> 00:05:21.369
(If Tankhun really exists, )

00:05:22.315 --> 00:05:23.849
(then you’re probably not Tankhun.)

00:05:30.297 --> 00:05:33.073
POLICE STATION

00:05:48.595 --> 00:05:49.595
Why are you here?

00:05:50.315 --> 00:05:51.385
Got a ticket?

00:05:51.521 --> 00:05:53.193
If it’s a ticket, I can afford it.

00:05:54.017 --> 00:05:55.289
Why would I be waiting for you?

00:05:57.285 --> 00:05:58.649
Then say what you want.

00:05:59.155 --> 00:06:00.049
But if you can’t have it

00:06:00.073 --> 00:06:01.073
then don’t blame me.

00:06:06.455 --> 00:06:07.769
I want the details

00:06:07.793 --> 00:06:10.313
of the 2 murder and dismemberment cases
that happened yesterday.

00:06:11.805 --> 00:06:13.281
To serve it to your journalist?

00:06:13.595 --> 00:06:15.473
As a criminologist,

00:06:16.125 --> 00:06:17.457
I want to solve this case.

00:06:18.585 --> 00:06:19.977
As a police officer,

00:06:20.335 --> 00:06:21.681
I think you’re being weird.

00:06:23.245 --> 00:06:25.265
Not as weird as finding 2 bodies

00:06:25.297 --> 00:06:27.265
in 2 luggage on the same day.

00:06:27.729 --> 00:06:29.725
The murderer is planning something

00:06:30.195 --> 00:06:31.569
And it won’t stop here.

00:06:32.295 --> 00:06:33.297
Don’t you think so?

00:06:42.405 --> 00:06:43.537
Let’s talk inside.

00:06:46.545 --> 00:06:48.081
I want to help Botpleng.

00:06:48.129 --> 00:06:49.745
If what you’re trying to find

00:06:49.777 --> 00:06:52.017
is connected to the fact that Botpleng
used to live here,

00:06:52.521 --> 00:06:54.525
then I’ll help you find out the truth.

00:06:55.465 --> 00:06:56.673
Also,

00:06:56.725 --> 00:06:57.925
you’ve just moved here, right?

00:06:58.241 --> 00:06:59.801
Don’t you have to put out achievements?

00:07:00.275 --> 00:07:01.297
Wouldn’t it be better

00:07:01.725 --> 00:07:02.765
to have me help you think?

00:07:04.475 --> 00:07:06.937
I have nothing against you helping.

00:07:07.769 --> 00:07:09.765
But if the result shows that

00:07:09.793 --> 00:07:13.065
Botpleng or people close to him
is the suspect,

00:07:14.005 --> 00:07:15.017
would you be okay with that?

00:07:15.033 --> 00:07:17.257
I don’t mix personal and work matters.

00:07:19.095 --> 00:07:20.257
One more thing,

00:07:20.825 --> 00:07:21.993
I’m sure

00:07:22.355 --> 00:07:23.673
that Pleng is not the culprit.

00:07:35.905 --> 00:07:37.905
Then welcome to the team.

00:07:38.545 --> 00:07:40.009
Adviser Tankhun.

00:07:47.561 --> 00:07:49.565
But let me ruin your confidence a little.

00:07:50.785 --> 00:07:53.033
The link between the victims in both cases

00:07:53.725 --> 00:07:57.297
is that they both worked for Botpleng’s family.

00:07:59.035 --> 00:08:00.081
The first victim

00:08:00.445 --> 00:08:02.753
took care of the Thayadon house.

00:08:03.875 --> 00:08:05.329
While the second victim

00:08:06.885 --> 00:08:09.089
used to work for Botpleng’s father.

00:08:13.915 --> 00:08:15.001
I hope you

00:08:15.595 --> 00:08:18.097
will be able to separate
work and personal matters.

00:08:22.095 --> 00:08:23.633
Thank you for the coffee.

00:08:45.873 --> 00:08:47.875
Is Korat your backyard?

00:08:48.765 --> 00:08:50.177
What if I say

00:08:50.705 --> 00:08:51.705
I didn’t go back?

00:08:54.125 --> 00:08:55.881
Not you acting all weird, too.

00:08:56.685 --> 00:08:58.161
I’m stressed out enough.

00:09:02.965 --> 00:09:03.965
Hold on.

00:09:04.935 --> 00:09:06.361
Did you sleep with him?

00:09:06.735 --> 00:09:07.833
Are you out of your mind?

00:09:08.705 --> 00:09:09.705
Well…

00:09:10.125 --> 00:09:12.089
You only came back in the morning.

00:09:12.645 --> 00:09:14.065
Unless you guys happened to hook up

00:09:14.845 --> 00:09:16.605
what else is there to be stressed out about?

00:09:21.377 --> 00:09:23.375
Do you think scars can go away?

00:09:24.105 --> 00:09:25.105
Is it deep?

00:09:25.285 --> 00:09:27.125
Nowadays, laser treatments can fix it for you.

00:09:32.665 --> 00:09:33.665
Hey!

00:09:34.325 --> 00:09:36.097
Was it so rough that you hurt yourself?

00:09:36.129 --> 00:09:36.737
Damn you!

00:09:36.761 --> 00:09:37.553
That’s not it!

00:09:37.585 --> 00:09:38.585
Oh?

00:09:39.965 --> 00:09:41.137
I’m stressed out

00:09:41.555 --> 00:09:42.857
because there wasn’t any scar.

00:09:50.305 --> 00:09:51.377
No scar?

00:09:52.915 --> 00:09:54.089
What are you talking about?

00:09:57.585 --> 00:10:00.769
The diary says Tankhun has
a deep scar on his wrist.

00:10:01.725 --> 00:10:03.353
But this Tankhun doesn’t have it.

00:10:07.095 --> 00:10:08.329
Then it’s good

00:10:08.361 --> 00:10:09.641
that you haven’t slept with him.

00:10:10.405 --> 00:10:12.561
Because if he’s able to lie to you this well,

00:10:13.325 --> 00:10:16.193
when he said he isn’t the murderer,

00:10:17.075 --> 00:10:18.553
he could be lying to you then, too.

00:10:22.145 --> 00:10:23.145
What are you on about?

00:10:25.645 --> 00:10:27.289
Think carefully.

00:10:28.245 --> 00:10:30.073
Isn’t it too much of a coincidence?

00:10:30.585 --> 00:10:32.201
That you met Tankhun

00:10:32.225 --> 00:10:33.425
and the body at the same time?

00:10:34.665 --> 00:10:36.905
What if Tankhun were the murderer

00:10:37.795 --> 00:10:39.473
and he was using you as a witness?

00:10:43.805 --> 00:10:45.177
Also,

00:10:45.445 --> 00:10:46.897
when the second body that

00:10:46.929 --> 00:10:48.665
died exactly like the first one was found,

00:10:49.645 --> 00:10:51.681
Tankhun also has an alibi

00:10:51.721 --> 00:10:52.721
which is you.

00:10:57.585 --> 00:10:59.209
Isn’t that too much of a coincidence?

00:11:07.885 --> 00:11:09.329
POLICE STATION

00:11:09.355 --> 00:11:12.057
For both bodies found in the luggage,

00:11:12.415 --> 00:11:14.505
we found a relation

00:11:14.537 --> 00:11:17.097
that they were done by the same murderer.

00:11:18.335 --> 00:11:20.417
Therefore, we can conclude that

00:11:20.433 --> 00:11:22.377
the two murder cases

00:11:22.895 --> 00:11:24.921
are part of a serial killing case.

00:11:26.695 --> 00:11:29.681
So today, we invited the press here
to ask for cooperation

00:11:29.713 --> 00:11:33.257
to report necessary information only.

00:11:33.289 --> 00:11:35.689
So as not to impact
the search for the murderer

00:11:36.081 --> 00:11:38.085
who murdered the victims professionally.

00:11:39.375 --> 00:11:40.375
Excuse me.

00:11:41.325 --> 00:11:43.761
Are you saying that we, the press,

00:11:43.793 --> 00:11:46.025
are obstructing the search for the murderer?

00:11:47.805 --> 00:11:50.017
Don’t you think that’s blaming the press

00:11:50.041 --> 00:11:51.249
more than necessary?

00:11:51.695 --> 00:11:53.297
I understand

00:11:53.321 --> 00:11:56.241
that the press has its ethics to uphold.

00:11:57.555 --> 00:12:00.521
Still, the police confirm that
this is not blaming

00:12:00.553 --> 00:12:02.353
but asking for cooperation.

00:12:02.393 --> 00:12:04.153
So that no other fatal incidents will occur.

00:12:05.525 --> 00:12:08.521
This method has been discussed

00:12:08.561 --> 00:12:10.185
with our criminologist.

00:12:10.905 --> 00:12:12.097
Professor Tankhun.

00:12:28.801 --> 00:12:31.001
Hello, I’m Tankhun.

00:12:31.025 --> 00:12:34.425
Criminologist on criminal psychology
and criminal behavior.

00:12:35.355 --> 00:12:36.721
The adviser of this case.

00:12:42.265 --> 00:12:44.425
The autopsy confirms that

00:12:44.465 --> 00:12:45.905
both bodies died in the same manner.

00:12:45.937 --> 00:12:47.833
That is strangling with garrote knots.

00:12:47.881 --> 00:12:50.305
The bodies are then dismembered.

00:12:50.665 --> 00:12:52.201
The murder was done professionally.

00:12:52.495 --> 00:12:54.329
Everything was done decisively.

00:12:54.361 --> 00:12:55.361
No hesitation.

00:12:55.635 --> 00:12:57.673
The relation between the two bodies

00:12:58.415 --> 00:13:00.025
are that both of them

00:13:00.057 --> 00:13:01.761
used to work for the Thayadon family.

00:13:02.185 --> 00:13:03.185
Yes.

00:13:03.835 --> 00:13:04.873
The Thayadon family.

00:13:05.635 --> 00:13:08.577
And both victims are locals of the same area.

00:13:09.045 --> 00:13:10.409
A lot of murderers

00:13:10.625 --> 00:13:14.065
choose their victims
from the same province or hometown.

00:13:14.315 --> 00:13:16.089
But there can also be other reasons

00:13:16.113 --> 00:13:17.737
which we still don’t know about.

00:13:18.135 --> 00:13:20.281
Then what do you think was the motive?

00:13:23.121 --> 00:13:25.125
This is a murder with purpose.

00:13:25.865 --> 00:13:27.993
But we have to figure out the killing motive.

00:13:28.033 --> 00:13:29.625
Whether it’s revenge,

00:13:29.657 --> 00:13:30.657
cover up,

00:13:31.195 --> 00:13:32.481
or just for pleasure.

00:13:32.841 --> 00:13:34.845
But for a murderer this skilled,

00:13:35.715 --> 00:13:37.401
they must have been paid to kill.

00:13:37.715 --> 00:13:39.825
The strange thing is putting both bodies out

00:13:39.857 --> 00:13:41.129
to expose them.

00:13:41.405 --> 00:13:42.885
As if to mock the police’s authority.

00:13:42.921 --> 00:13:43.993
That’s right.

00:13:44.325 --> 00:13:45.529
It’s so crazy.

00:13:45.561 --> 00:13:47.489
Putting the bodies out in the open,

00:13:47.725 --> 00:13:49.129
as if they wanted us to find them.

00:13:49.505 --> 00:13:50.505
Then what do we do next?

00:13:53.925 --> 00:13:55.681
The press already knew about the bodies.

00:13:56.845 --> 00:13:58.345
We have to control the press first.

00:13:59.645 --> 00:14:00.889
(Based on the discussion

00:14:00.905 --> 00:14:02.089
with Professor Tankhun, )

00:14:02.125 --> 00:14:05.289
We realize that this murderer is daring,

00:14:05.325 --> 00:14:06.325
fearless

00:14:06.785 --> 00:14:08.673
and enjoy mocking the police’s authority.

00:14:08.729 --> 00:14:10.737
So I ask the press for cooperation

00:14:10.761 --> 00:14:12.681
in reporting this case
only as much as necessary.

00:14:13.735 --> 00:14:17.001
You can report the discovery of the bodies

00:14:17.025 --> 00:14:17.833
but I hope you would avoid

00:14:17.857 --> 00:14:19.945
the mention of the serial murder.

00:14:21.045 --> 00:14:23.513
Since it would bring pleasure to the murderer

00:14:24.217 --> 00:14:26.215
and make them commit the crime again.

00:14:26.405 --> 00:14:28.377
You want us to hide it from the people

00:14:28.393 --> 00:14:30.537
that there is a murderer in the area?

00:14:30.577 --> 00:14:33.281
I’ll say it one last time.

00:14:34.155 --> 00:14:36.729
That this is the best way

00:14:36.753 --> 00:14:38.725
to handle this murderer.

00:14:40.995 --> 00:14:43.025
Thank you all in advance,

00:14:43.065 --> 00:14:44.193
for your cooperation.

00:14:44.689 --> 00:14:46.833
Have a safe journey back.

00:14:46.865 --> 00:14:47.337
Oh?

00:14:47.785 --> 00:14:48.961
We haven’t got any news.

00:14:53.245 --> 00:14:54.537
We didn’t get anything out of it.

00:14:54.561 --> 00:14:55.561
Yeah.

00:15:03.675 --> 00:15:06.353
POLICE STATION

00:15:07.455 --> 00:15:08.577
So damn weird.

00:15:08.885 --> 00:15:10.433
Asking for cooperation

00:15:10.775 --> 00:15:12.081
but not telling us anything.

00:15:12.745 --> 00:15:13.377
Only the excuse of

00:15:13.401 --> 00:15:15.057
“protection, protection”.

00:15:16.385 --> 00:15:18.081
As if they’re trying to shut the press up.

00:15:18.735 --> 00:15:19.881
Is that even acceptable?

00:15:21.885 --> 00:15:22.885
Hey!

00:15:23.335 --> 00:15:24.335
Pleng!

00:15:24.805 --> 00:15:26.233
That bastard Pleng.

00:15:27.145 --> 00:15:28.145
Where did he go?

00:15:32.135 --> 00:15:33.135
Inspector.

00:15:34.125 --> 00:15:35.649
I have something to ask.

00:15:36.121 --> 00:15:38.125
Didn’t you understand the word
“one last time”?

00:15:38.153 --> 00:15:40.125
You can keep quiet if you want

00:15:40.555 --> 00:15:41.809
but if you’re trying to shut the press up,

00:15:41.833 --> 00:15:44.089
and keeping the people in the dark
about the serial killer,

00:15:44.105 --> 00:15:45.113
that’s unacceptable.

00:15:47.805 --> 00:15:50.073
Then, if the murderer can’t be arrested.

00:15:50.465 --> 00:15:52.217
The people are in more danger.

00:15:53.041 --> 00:15:55.281
Would you, Mr. Press,
be able to handle the consequences?

00:15:59.465 --> 00:16:00.809
So that means you already knew

00:16:01.425 --> 00:16:02.697
who the murderer is, right?

00:16:10.729 --> 00:16:11.257
Urgh!

00:16:11.561 --> 00:16:12.617
That’s you!

00:16:13.085 --> 00:16:15.025
You’re causing more people to die.

00:16:15.845 --> 00:16:16.881
What are you guys doing?

00:16:20.645 --> 00:16:22.057
It’s true what you said.

00:16:22.695 --> 00:16:24.449
Some people won’t agree with us

00:16:24.473 --> 00:16:25.537
and try to get in the way.

00:16:27.875 --> 00:16:28.875
Come with me.

00:16:41.645 --> 00:16:42.645
Are you aware

00:16:43.033 --> 00:16:44.689
that what you did

00:16:44.721 --> 00:16:46.145
was threatening Inspector Dao?

00:16:46.725 --> 00:16:47.905
And you know what?

00:16:48.275 --> 00:16:50.441
The police are threatening the press, too.

00:16:51.465 --> 00:16:53.913
Don’t the people have the right
to know what’s going on?

00:16:54.205 --> 00:16:56.889
Especially about a serial killer
which is lurking among us.

00:16:57.297 --> 00:16:59.295
The police should inform everyone
to stay alert.

00:17:02.165 --> 00:17:03.165
You’re right.

00:17:03.885 --> 00:17:05.113
It should be that way,

00:17:05.445 --> 00:17:06.937
if the murderer killed and hid the bodies

00:17:06.953 --> 00:17:07.953
like in the other cases.

00:17:08.445 --> 00:17:11.161
But this murderer wanted to show off
the bodies of the victims.

00:17:11.193 --> 00:17:13.265
If you make this case blow up,

00:17:13.535 --> 00:17:15.257
and encourage the murderer to kill more,

00:17:15.705 --> 00:17:17.169
can you handle the consequences?

00:17:21.935 --> 00:17:23.689
I didn’t know it’d be that bad.

00:17:25.685 --> 00:17:26.685
I’m sorry.

00:17:29.225 --> 00:17:30.825
The one you should apologize to

00:17:30.857 --> 00:17:32.881
is Inspector Dao, not me.

00:17:37.009 --> 00:17:38.457
But you’re angry too.

00:17:39.045 --> 00:17:40.889
Your brows are tied together.

00:17:42.065 --> 00:17:43.193
I’m not angry.

00:17:44.365 --> 00:17:45.365
If you’re not angry,

00:17:45.925 --> 00:17:47.521
then would you go somewhere with me?

00:17:50.035 --> 00:17:51.035
Yeah.

00:17:51.485 --> 00:17:52.485
Fine.

00:17:53.365 --> 00:17:54.617
I’ll go

00:17:55.445 --> 00:17:57.009
if it’s interesting enough.

00:17:57.455 --> 00:17:58.657
I guarantee

00:17:59.649 --> 00:18:01.645
it’s somewhere that will get you in the mood.

00:18:03.405 --> 00:18:04.953
Interesting enough?

00:18:18.175 --> 00:18:19.281
My mom used to say,

00:18:20.017 --> 00:18:22.015
desserts can get you in a good mood.

00:18:22.795 --> 00:18:24.113
Eat a lot.

00:18:24.995 --> 00:18:26.435
So you won’t be angry at me anymore.

00:18:41.525 --> 00:18:42.525
Oh?

00:18:43.937 --> 00:18:44.937
So sour.

00:18:45.285 --> 00:18:46.553
I thought you would like it.

00:18:47.655 --> 00:18:50.097
(Tankhun had star fruit for the first time.)

00:18:50.525 --> 00:18:51.697
(He loved it.)

00:18:56.175 --> 00:18:57.649
I remember your mom said

00:18:57.985 --> 00:18:59.985
you like chocolate cake.

00:19:02.845 --> 00:19:04.217
That’s what mom says.

00:19:05.055 --> 00:19:06.673
But the more I have it,

00:19:07.165 --> 00:19:09.449
I think I like fruit cakes.

00:19:10.045 --> 00:19:11.305
It’s refreshing.

00:19:12.593 --> 00:19:13.745
But just as people say.

